# ── Atelier config ──  copy to .env.local (never commit .env.local). Every value here is
# OPTIONAL — the app runs with NO .env.local at all. Model auth is NOT an env key: it's the
# CLI login (see below). Set these only to override a default or gate/share the board.

# MODEL AUTH — there is NO API key to set here. Every model call runs through the Claude Code
# harness, which uses each CLI's OWN login:
#   • Claude models (Opus/Sonnet)      → log into the `claude` CLI (Claude Code).
#   • GLM / Qwen / Kimi (via Ollama)   → log into the `ollama` CLI (it backs `ollama launch claude`).
# Log into whichever CLI matches the model you pick in the UI. (OLLAMA_API_KEY is NOT read by
# any code — it's legacy; leaving it set or unset changes nothing.)

# OPTIONAL. Where run workspaces (git worktrees + captures) live. Defaults to
# ./.factory/workspaces. Point at a big/external volume for heavy runs.
# FACTORY_WORKSPACES_DIR=/Volumes/External/atelier-workspaces

# OPTIONAL. Share ONE Atelier with your team: set a password and the whole app is
# gated behind it (an unlock screen sets a cookie). Lets you safely expose the board
# over the LAN or a tunnel (cloudflared/ngrok) so everyone reviews + comments on the
# SAME loops. Leave unset for local-only use (then there's no gate).
# ACCESS_PASSWORD=

# OPTIONAL. Secret for the localhost tool bridge (/api/internal/tool, which can run shell).
# If unset, a strong RANDOM per-process secret is generated (fail closed — no guessable default),
# which is fine for a single long-running instance. setup.sh also writes one into .env.local.
# Set your own ONLY for a multi-instance or restart-stable deployment where every process/worker
# must share the same value.
# FACTORY_INTERNAL_SECRET=

# OPTIONAL. Path to Chrome (for QA capture + test-drive). Defaults to the macOS
# system Chrome. Set if yours is elsewhere (Linux: chromium works).
# CHROME_PATH=/Applications/Google Chrome.app/Contents/MacOS/Google Chrome

# OPTIONAL. Hostname teammates should use to reach test-drive dev servers on this
# machine — a DNS name, Tailscale name, or IP. Defaults to the auto-detected LAN IP,
# which is often wrong/unreachable on a cloud VM. Used only for the shareable URL.
# FACTORY_PUBLIC_HOST=atelier.internal.example.com

# OPTIONAL. Max loops running at once (default 1 — runs queue and serialize).
# FACTORY_MAX_CONCURRENT_RUNS=1

# OPTIONAL. Comma-separated hostnames/IPs you reach the shared dev server from over
# the LAN or a Tailscale tailnet (your MagicDNS name, tailnet IP, .local name). Next
# 16 dev allow-lists these so HMR stays connected. Machine-specific — keep it here in
# .env.local, not in the committed next.config.ts.
# FACTORY_DEV_ORIGINS=your-machine.tailXXXXX.ts.net,your-machine.local,100.x.y.z
